<section class="experience">
  <h2>Experience</h2>
  
  <article class="job">
    <h3>Studio Aisha</h3>
    <p class="tenure">January 2021 - Current</p>
    <p>After over a decade working in-house, I started Studio Aisha because I wanted to get closer to real user problems and work with clients who genuinely want to get it right. I missed being able to choose the work and the people, and consulting gave me that. My work spans research, UX strategy, information architecture and experience design, and my clients range from mature startups and mid to large companies to global nonprofit organizations.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Booking.com</h3>
    <p class="tenure">July 2017 - December 2020</p>
    <p>I joined as a UX designer and grew into a senior designer and team lead. This is where I really deepened my research skills, working closely with product managers and user researchers to understand how people actually behaved and build strategies from that understanding rather than just reacting to surface-level data.</p>
    <p>My work spanned complex, high-traffic customer journeys, from reducing harmful booking behaviors to launching and evolving the Genius loyalty program. I focused on understanding what was driving user decisions, building cross-funnel roadmaps from those insights, and designing systems that could support experimentation without compromising user trust.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Skillcrush</h3>
    <p class="tenure">January 2015 - June 2017</p>
    <p>As lead designer, I led a small team working closely with stakeholders to research, test and ship products that met user needs while strengthening a clear and consistent brand identity. I also helped design the learning platform itself and served as the subject matter expert for two online design courses I helped build, an Intro to Responsive Design and an Intro to Visual and UX Design, each consisting of three classes.</p>
  </article>

  <article class="job">
    <h3>Penton Media</h3>
    <p class="tenure">November 2010 - July 2014</p>
    <p>As a UX designer, I partnered closely with project managers and developers to design new functionality and layouts for custom Drupal-based CMSs. I was one of two designers responsible for migrating over 80 legacy sites to a new CMS, designing custom modules per site and advising on layout and customization.</p>
  </article>

